Eric Bridger eric@gomoos.org  eric.bridger@gmail.com
Gulf of Maine Ocean Observing System / North East Regional Association of Coastal Ocean Observing Systems.
File List
    * oostethys_sos.cgi  -  the CGI script
    * sos_config.xml - empty configuration file.
    * example_sos_config.xml -  An example config file using values from GoMOOS
    * sosGetCapabilities.xml - 1.0 template
    * sosGetObservation.xml - 1.0 template
    * sosDescribeSystem.xml - 1.0 template
    * difGetCapabilities.xml - DIF template
    * difGetObservation.xml - DIF template
    * difDescribeSystem.xml - DIF template
	* README - This file
	* docs/INSTALL - Basic install instructions
	* docs/INSTALL_ASCII - Setting up to serve observations stored in ASCII text files
	* docs/INSTALL_RDBMS - Setting up to serve observations stored in a relational database via DBI
	* docs/INSTALL_MODULES - How to install some required PERL modules
	* docs/UPGRADES - How to upgrade from previous PERL installations while saving local configuration edits
	* docs/SOS_with_Perl_MS_Windows - Notes on installing on a Windows server using ActiveState PERL.

OOSTethys Project code repository: http://code.google.com/p/oostethys/

More about the OOSTethys Project: http://www.oostethys.org/

PERL documents via HTML: http://www.oostethys.org/downloads/sos-cookbook-perl
   (Note: code should not be downloaded from www.oostethys.org, use code.google.com)

The PERL SOS toolkit serves observation data from either ASCII text files or a relational database through the SOS interface, and is written entirely in PERL.

see The OOSTethys project page or  docs/INSTALL, docs/UPGRADES, docs/INSTALL_ASCII or docs/INSTALL_RDBMS for further instructions.
########################################
Wed Nov 25 09:52:14 EST 2009  Version 1.0.0
Changes:
This version includes major changes but should work with existing configuration files and/or customized database query functions.
*  Support for the NOAA IOOS DIF 0.6.1 GML schema outputs. new dif* templates included.
*  Support for mapping of IOOS DIF core variables to mulitple atomic observedProperites or not. If not traditional CF observed Properties will be used.
*  Compliance with the OGC's CITE SOS 1.0.0 Testing suite as described here:  http://cite.opengeospatial.org/betaTesting
*  That testing resulted in:
*     Improved support for OGC standard Exceptions.
*     Greatly improved support for OGC XML POST requests.
*     Checks for proper: procedure,  featureOfInterest, outputFormat, responseFormat, srsName.
*     These values are parsed from the sosGetCapabilities.xml template.
########################################
Nov. 4 2009 Version 0.5.1
Changes:
* Fixed namespaces in xml templates
* namespaces for XPath are gotten from template root namespaces
* blockSeparator and tokenSeparator are not retrieved from templates
* time input parameter is now eventTime (case insensitive)

